## 5. Collection Details

---

### 5.1 `configs`

> Stores clinic/doctor credentials and settings. One document per clinic.

| Field | Type | Constraint | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `email` | String | **PK**, Required, Unique | Login email / doctor identifier |
| `password` | String | Required | Login password (plain text — consider hashing) |
| `clinicName` | String | Default: `"MedRecord Pro Clinic"` | Display name |
| `address` | String | — | Clinic physical address |
| `phone` | String | — | Clinic contact number |
| `isActive` | Boolean | Default: `true` | Account active flag (used by auth middleware) |

**Relationships:** None — fully standalone.
**Seeding:** Auto-creates `dr.aarti@medcore.in` on first run if empty.

---

### 5.2 `patients`

> Core entity. Every visit, appointment, and report links back to a patient via `mobile`.

| Field | Type | Constraint | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `mobile` | String | **PK**, Required, Unique | Primary identifier — patient's mobile number |
| `name` | String | — | Full name |
| [age](file:///c:/Users/bhavi/Desktop/bhavik%20docs/Digitifi/works/emr%20software/services/db.ts#35-47) | Number | — | Age in years |
| `dob` | String | — | Date of birth (ISO string) |
| `gender` | String | Enum: `Male / Female / Other` | Biological gender |
| `bloodGroup` | String | — | e.g. `"B+"` |
| `occupation` | String | — | Patient's occupation |
| `address` | String | — | Street/building address |
| `area` | String | — | Locality / area |
| `city` | String | — | City |
| `state` | String | — | State |
| [pin](file:///c:/Users/bhavi/Desktop/bhavik%20docs/Digitifi/works/emr%20software/services/db.ts#79-80) | String | — | Postal / ZIP code |
| `country` | String | — | Country |
| `email` | String | — | Patient email address |
| `allergyOther` | String | — | Non-medicine allergies |
| `allergyMedicine` | String | — | Medicine/drug allergies |
| `habits.smoke` | String | — | Smoking habit |
| `habits.alcohol` | String | — | Alcohol habit |
| `habits.drugAbuse` | String | — | Drug abuse history |
| `referredBy` | String | — | Referring doctor/source |
| `createdDate` | String | — | Registration date (ISO string) |
| `familyId` | String | **FK → families.id**, Nullable | Family group this patient belongs to |
| `pastHistoryNotes` | String | — | Chronic history / past medical notes |
| `updatedAt` | Date | Auto | Last modified timestamp |

**Relationships:**
- `familyId` → `families.id` *(optional — a patient may or may not be in a family group)*
- Referenced by: `visits.patientMobile`, `appointments.patientMobile`, `reports.patientMobile`, `families.members[].mobile`

---

### 5.3 `families`

> Groups related patients together (e.g. family units). A patient can belong to at most one family.

| Field | Type | Constraint | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| [id](file:///c:/Users/bhavi/Desktop/bhavik%20docs/Digitifi/works/emr%20software/server.js#281-321) | String | **PK**, Required, Unique | App-generated family ID |
| `name` | String | — | Optional family group name |
| `members` | FamilyMember[] | — | Array of `{ mobile (FK), relationship }` |
| `updatedAt` | Date | Auto | Last modified timestamp |

**Relationships:**
- `members[].mobile` → `patients.mobile` *(each member must be an existing patient)*
- Referenced by: `patients.familyId`

**Business Rules:**
- A family must have at least 2 members to be meaningful. Families with ≤ 1 member are auto-deleted on cascade.
- When a patient is deleted, they are removed from `members[]` in all families.

---

### 5.4 `visits`

> Records a single clinical encounter (consultation). The richest document — contains embedded medicines, vitals, and billing.

| Field | Type | Constraint | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| [id](file:///c:/Users/bhavi/Desktop/bhavik%20docs/Digitifi/works/emr%20software/server.js#281-321) | String | **PK**, Required, Unique | App-generated visit ID |
| `patientMobile` | String | **FK → patients.mobile**, Required | Which patient this visit belongs to |
| [date](file:///c:/Users/bhavi/Desktop/bhavik%20docs/Digitifi/works/emr%20software/services/db.ts#199-205) | String | — | Visit date+time (ISO string) |
| `diagnosis` | String | — | Primary diagnosis text |
| `medicines` | Medicine[] | Subdoc array | Prescribed medicines *(see §4.1)* |
| `reportsOrdered` | String[] | — | List of tests ordered (text, not uploaded files) |
| `reportIds` | String[] | **FK[] → reports.id** | IDs of uploaded report files linked to this visit |
| `amount` | Number | — | Consultation / billing amount (₹) |
| `paymentMethod` | String | Enum: `Cash / GPay / UPI / Card / Due Payment` | How the patient paid |
| `paymentStatus` | String | Enum: `Paid / Pending` | Payment settlement status |
| `prescriptionNotes` | String | — | General instructions for the prescription |
| `vitals` | Vitals | Subdoc | Clinical measurements *(see §4.2)* |
| `updatedAt` | Date | Auto | Last modified timestamp |

**Relationships:**
- `patientMobile` → `patients.mobile` *(required — every visit must belong to a patient)*
- `reportIds[]` → `reports.id` *(optional — links uploaded files to this visit)*

---

### 5.5 `appointments`

> Scheduled future appointments. Separate from visits (appointments are bookings; visits are completed encounters).

| Field | Type | Constraint | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| [id](file:///c:/Users/bhavi/Desktop/bhavik%20docs/Digitifi/works/emr%20software/server.js#281-321) | String | **PK**, Required, Unique | App-generated appointment ID |
| `patientMobile` | String | **FK → patients.mobile**, Required | Which patient this appointment is for |
| [date](file:///c:/Users/bhavi/Desktop/bhavik%20docs/Digitifi/works/emr%20software/services/db.ts#199-205) | String | — | Appointment date (`YYYY-MM-DD`) |
| `time` | String | — | Appointment time (`HH:MM`) |
| `reason` | String | — | Reason / chief complaint |
| `status` | String | Enum: `Scheduled / Completed / Missed / Cancelled` | Current appointment status |
| `updatedAt` | Date | Auto | Last modified timestamp |

**Relationships:**
- `patientMobile` → `patients.mobile` *(required)*

---

### 5.6 `reports`

> Uploaded medical files (labs, X-rays, prescriptions, past records). Stored as Base64.

| Field | Type | Constraint | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| [id](file:///c:/Users/bhavi/Desktop/bhavik%20docs/Digitifi/works/emr%20software/server.js#281-321) | String | **PK**, Required, Unique | App-generated report ID |
| `patientMobile` | String | **FK → patients.mobile**, Required | Which patient this report belongs to |
| `type` | String | Enum: `Lab / Xray / Prescription / Other / Past Record` | Report category |
| `description` | String | — | Report description / summary |
| [date](file:///c:/Users/bhavi/Desktop/bhavik%20docs/Digitifi/works/emr%20software/services/db.ts#199-205) | String | — | Report date (ISO string) |
| `fileName` | String | — | Original uploaded file name |
| `fileData` | String | — | Base64-encoded file content |
| `updatedAt` | Date | Auto | Last modified timestamp |

**Relationships:**
- `patientMobile` → `patients.mobile` *(required)*
- Referenced by: `visits.reportIds[]` *(a visit can link to multiple reports)*

> ⚠️ `fileData` stores Base64 content — large files can significantly increase document size. The server uses `express.json({ limit: '100mb' })` to accommodate this.

---

### 5.7 `customdiagnoses`

> A user-maintained lookup table of custom diagnosis names not in the default list.

| Field | Type | Constraint | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `name` | String | **PK**, Required, Unique | The diagnosis term (e.g. `"Plantar Fasciitis"`) |
| `updatedAt` | Date | Auto | Last modified timestamp |

**Relationships:** None — fully standalone lookup table.

> **Frontend note:** The frontend stores these as a plain `string[]`. The server converts to/from `{ name }` documents transparently.

---

### 5.8 `templates`

> Preset treatment templates. When a doctor selects a diagnosis, the template auto-fills medicines and reports to order.

| Field | Type | Constraint | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `diagnosis` | String | **PK**, Required, Unique | Diagnosis name (the template key) |
| `defaultMedicines` | Medicine[] | Subdoc array | Pre-filled medicines *(same schema as Visit.medicines[])* |
| `defaultReports` | String[] | — | Pre-filled list of tests to order |
| `updatedAt` | Date | Auto | Last modified timestamp |

**Relationships:** None — standalone preset table.

